HEADWORD: Lernean
<hw>Ler*ne"an</hw> <pr>(l⟦etil⟧r*n⟦emac⟧"⟦ait⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[See <er>Lern⟦ae⟧a</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of a
family (<fam>Lern⟦ae⟧id⟦ae⟧</fam>) of parasitic Crustacea found attached
to fishes and other marine animals. Some species penetrate the skin and
flesh with the elongated head, and feed on the viscera. See
<xex>Illust.</xex> in Appendix.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

